      "question_id": "DISC-Q1",
      "category": "Discovery & Documentation",
      "category_id": "DISC",
      "title": "No automated API contract breaking-change detection in CI",
      "description": "The repository uses semantic versioning (v6.0-SNAPSHOT) and maintains comprehensive documentation. However, there is no automated breaking-change detection in CI (no japicmp, revapi, buf breaking, or consumer-driven contract tests). The CI pipeline validates compilation and tests but does not detect API-breaking changes to public connector interfaces before merge.",
      "gap": "No API compatibility checking tools (japicmp, revapi) or consumer-driven contract tests in CI pipeline. Public API surface changes could break downstream Flink applications without early detection.",
      "recommendation": "Add japicmp-maven-plugin or revapi-maven-plugin to CI for binary compatibility checks on public API classes.",
      "severity": "Medium",
      "priority": "P2",
      "effort": "Medium",
      "phase": 2,
      "evidence": {
        "file": ".github/workflows/common.yml",
        "lines": null
      },
      "ara_metadata": {
        "native_severity": "RISK-QUALITY",
        "safety_impact": false,
        "remediation_timeline": "60–90 days",
        "compensating_controls": [
          "ArchUnit architecture tests enforce structural rules in each module",
          "Maven shade plugin with relocation prevents classpath conflicts",
          "Flink connector parent POM enforces dependency convergence"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "question_id": "OBS-Q1",
      "category": "Observability",
      "category_id": "OBS",
      "title": "No structured logging or distributed tracing hooks",
      "description": "The library uses SLF4J with plain-text PatternLayout logging. Root logger is OFF in production JARs (correct for library). No structured JSON logging, no MDC/NDC context enrichment, and no OpenTelemetry/X-Ray instrumentation hooks are provided. The library does not propagate or enrich trace context.",
      "gap": "No trace context propagation or structured logging support for consuming applications. Consuming applications cannot correlate connector-internal log events with their own trace context without additional instrumentation work.",
      "recommendation": "Add MDC context propagation for trace IDs in key connector operations (source reads, sink writes) to allow consuming Flink applications to correlate connector activity with their distributed traces.",
      "severity": "Medium",
      "priority": "P2",
      "effort": "Medium",
      "phase": 2,
      "evidence": {
        "file": "flink-connector-aws-base/src/main/resources/log4j2.properties",
        "lines": null
      },
      "ara_metadata": {
        "native_severity": "RISK-QUALITY",
        "safety_impact": false,
        "remediation_timeline": "90–120 days",
        "compensating_controls": [
          "SLF4J abstraction allows consuming applications to configure any logging backend including JSON formatters",
          "Flink's built-in metrics system provides operational visibility"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "question_id": "OBS-Q2",
      "category": "Observability",
      "category_id": "OBS",
      "title": "No recommended alerting thresholds documented",
      "description": "The library emits Flink metrics (records sent, bytes, latency, errors) but does not provide pre-configured alerting thresholds or documentation of recommended alert configurations for consuming applications.",
      "gap": "No monitoring/alerting guidance in documentation. Consumers must independently determine appropriate error rate and latency thresholds for connector operations.",
      "recommendation": "Add a Monitoring & Alerting section to connector documentation recommending specific Flink metrics to alert on (e.g., numRecordsSendErrors, currentSendTime) with suggested thresholds.",
      "severity": "Medium",
      "priority": "P2",
      "effort": "Low",
